<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Olympic Peninsula Overland Trip — June 18-22, 2026</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://unpkg.com/leaflet@1.9.4/dist/leaflet.css" />
    <script src="https://unpkg.com/leaflet@1.9.4/dist/leaflet.js"></script>
    <style>
        * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
        body {
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', -apple-system, sans-serif;
            background: #1a1a2e;
            color: #e0e0e0;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }
        .hero {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f3443 0%, #34e89e22 100%),
                        url('data:image/svg+xml,<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 1440 320"><path fill="%23ffffff11" d="M0,160L48,176C96,192,192,224,288,213.3C384,203,480,149,576,138.7C672,128,768,160,864,181.3C960,203,1056,213,1152,197.3C1248,181,1344,139,1392,117.3L1440,96L1440,320L1392,320C1344,320,1248,320,1152,320C1056,320,960,320,864,320C768,320,672,320,576,320C480,320,384,320,288,320C192,320,96,320,48,320L0,320Z"></path></svg>') no-repeat bottom;
            padding: 60px 40px;
            text-align: center;
            border-bottom: 3px solid #34e89e;
        }
        .hero h1 {
            font-size: 2.8rem;
            color: #fff;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            text-shadow: 0 2px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
        }
        .hero .subtitle {
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            color: #34e89e;
            font-weight: 300;
        }
        .hero .dates {
            margin-top: 15px;
            font-size: 1rem;
            color: #aaa;
        }
        .container { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 40px 20px; }

        /* Tab Navigation */
        .tab-nav {
            display: flex;
            gap: 4px;
            margin-bottom: 0;
            background: #16213e;
            border-radius: 12px 12px 0 0;
            padding: 8px 8px 0;
            overflow: hidden;
        }
        .tab-btn {
            flex: 1;
            padding: 16px 24px;
            background: #1a1a2e;
            border: none;
            color: #888;
            font-size: 1rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            cursor: pointer;
            border-radius: 8px 8px 0 0;
            transition: all 0.3s;
        }
        .tab-btn.active {
            background: #0f3443;
            color: #34e89e;
            box-shadow: 0 -2px 10px rgba(52,232,158,0.2);
        }
        .tab-btn:hover:not(.active) { color: #ccc; background: #1e2a4a; }

        .tab-content { display: none; background: #0f3443; border-radius: 0 0 12px 12px; padding: 30px; }
        .tab-content.active { display: block; }

        /* Route Overview */
        .route-overview {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
            gap: 20px;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }
        .route-stat {
            background: #16213e;
            border-radius: 8px;
            padding: 15px 20px;
            border-left: 3px solid #34e89e;
        }
        .route-stat label { font-size: 0.8rem; text-transform: uppercase; color: #888; letter-spacing: 1px; }
        .route-stat .value { font-size: 1.3rem; color: #fff; font-weight: 600; margin-top: 4px; }

        /* Map Container */
        .map-container {
            border-radius: 12px;
            overflow: hidden;
            margin: 25px 0;
            border: 2px solid #34e89e33;
            height: 450px;
        }

        /* Day Cards */
        .day-card {
            background: #16213e;
            border-radius: 12px;
            margin-bottom: 25px;
            overflow: hidden;
            border: 1px solid #ffffff11;
            transition: transform 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
        }
        .day-card:hover {
            transform: translateY(-2px);
            box-shadow: 0 8px 25px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
        }
        .day-header {
            padding: 20px 25px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 20px;
            cursor: pointer;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a2540 0%, #16213e 100%);
        }
        .day-number {
            background: #34e89e;
            color: #0f3443;
            font-weight: 800;
            font-size: 1.4rem;
            width: 55px;
            height: 55px;
            border-radius: 50%;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            flex-shrink: 0;
        }
        .day-title h3 { color: #fff; font-size: 1.2rem; }
        .day-title .route-text { color: #34e89e; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-top: 3px; }
        .day-meta {
            margin-left: auto;
            text-align: right;
            flex-shrink: 0;
        }
        .day-meta .drive-time {
            background: #34e89e22;
            color: #34e89e;
            padding: 4px 12px;
            border-radius: 20px;
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            font-weight: 600;
        }
        .day-meta .distance {
            color: #888;
            font-size: 0.8rem;
            margin-top: 5px;
        }

        .day-body { padding: 0 25px 25px; }

        /* Timeline */
        .timeline {
            position: relative;
            padding-left: 30px;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }
        .timeline::before {
            content: '';
            position: absolute;
            left: 8px;
            top: 5px;
            bottom: 5px;
            width: 2px;
            background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #34e89e, #0f3443);
        }
        .timeline-item {
            position: relative;
            margin-bottom: 18px;
            padding-left: 15px;
        }
        .timeline-item::before {
            content: '';
            position: absolute;
            left: -26px;
            top: 8px;
            width: 10px;
            height: 10px;
            border-radius: 50%;
            background: #34e89e;
            border: 2px solid #0f3443;
        }
        .timeline-item.camp::before { background: #f39c12; border-color: #f39c12; width: 12px; height: 12px; left: -27px; }
        .timeline-time {
            font-size: 0.8rem;
            color: #34e89e;
            font-weight: 600;
            text-transform: uppercase;
        }
        .timeline-title { color: #fff; font-weight: 600; margin: 3px 0; }
        .timeline-desc { color: #aaa; font-size: 0.9rem; }

        /* Tags */
        .tag {
            display: inline-block;
            padding: 2px 10px;
            border-radius: 12px;
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            margin-right: 5px;
        }
        .tag-ocean { background: #0077b622; color: #4fc3f7; border: 1px solid #4fc3f744; }
        .tag-forest { background: #2e7d3222; color: #81c784; border: 1px solid #81c78444; }
        .tag-mountain { background: #5c6bc022; color: #9fa8da; border: 1px solid #9fa8da44; }
        .tag-camp { background: #f57c0022; color: #ffb74d; border: 1px solid #ffb74d44; }

        /* Camp Box */
        .camp-box {
            background: #f39c1211;
            border: 1px solid #f39c1244;
            border-radius: 8px;
            padding: 15px 20px;
            margin-top: 15px;
        }
        .camp-box h4 { color: #f39c12; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 8px; }
        .camp-box .primary { color: #fff; font-weight: 600; }
        .camp-box .backup { color: #888; font-size: 0.85rem; margin-top: 5px; }
        .camp-box .coords {
            font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
            font-size: 0.8rem;
            color: #34e89e;
            margin-top: 5px;
        }

        /* Directions Link */
        .directions-link {
            display: inline-flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 6px;
            background: #34e89e22;
            color: #34e89e;
            padding: 8px 16px;
            border-radius: 6px;
            text-decoration: none;
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            margin-top: 10px;
            transition: background 0.2s;
        }
        .directions-link:hover { background: #34e89e33; }

        /* Gear Section */
        .gear-section {
            background: #16213e;
            border-radius: 12px;
            padding: 30px;
            margin-top: 40px;
        }
        .gear-section h2 { color: #34e89e; margin-bottom: 20px; }
        .gear-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
            gap: 15px;
        }
        .gear-category h4 { color: #fff; margin-bottom: 8px; font-size: 0.95rem; }
        .gear-category ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
        .gear-category li { color: #aaa; font-size: 0.85rem; padding: 3px 0; padding-left: 15px; position: relative; }
        .gear-category li::before { content: '▸'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: #34e89e; }

        /* Notes */
        .notes-box {
            background: #f39c1211;
            border-left: 3px solid #f39c12;
            padding: 15px 20px;
            border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }
        .notes-box h4 { color: #f39c12; margin-bottom: 8px; }
        .notes-box p, .notes-box li { color: #ccc; font-size: 0.9rem; }

        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .hero h1 { font-size: 1.8rem; }
            .route-overview { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
            .day-header { flex-wrap: wrap; }
            .day-meta { margin-left: 0; margin-top: 10px; text-align: left; }
            .tab-btn { font-size: 0.85rem; padding: 12px 10px; }
            .map-container { height: 300px; }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="hero">
    <h1>🏔️ Olympic Peninsula Overland</h1>
    <div class="subtitle">Rainforest · Ocean · Mountains — A 5-Day Loop</div>
    <div class="dates">June 18–22, 2026 · Seattle + Portland Convergence</div>
</div>

<div class="container">

<!-- Tab Navigation -->
<div class="tab-nav">
    <button class="tab-btn active" onclick="switchTab('optionA')">Option A: Counter-Clockwise</button>
    <button class="tab-btn" onclick="switchTab('optionB')">Option B: Clockwise</button>
</div>

<!-- ==================== OPTION A ==================== -->
<div class="tab-content active" id="optionA">
    <h2 style="color:#34e89e; margin-bottom:5px;">Option A — Rainforest → Ocean → Mountains</h2>
    <p style="color:#aaa; margin-bottom:25px;">South-to-north arc. Meet at Quinault, end at Port Angeles. Builds from lush valleys to alpine vistas.</p>

    <div class="route-overview">
        <div class="route-stat"><label>Total Driving</label><div class="value">~8.5 hours over 4 days</div></div>
        <div class="route-stat"><label>Total Distance</label><div class="value">~320 miles (loop)</div></div>
        <div class="route-stat"><label>Max Single Day</label><div class="value">~3 hrs (Day 4)</div></div>
        <div class="route-stat"><label>Dispersed Sites</label><div class="value">4 nights, 3 areas</div></div>
    </div>

    <div class="map-container" id="mapA"></div>

    <!-- Day 1 -->
    <div class="day-card">
        <div class="day-header">
            <div class="day-number">1</div>
            <div class="day-title">
                <h3>Converge on Quinault Rainforest</h3>
                <div class="route-text">Seattle → Quinault &nbsp;|&nbsp; Portland → Quinault</div>
            </div>
            <div class="day-meta">
                <div class="drive-time">🚗 ~3–3.5 hrs</div>
                <div class="distance">Seattle: 145mi / Portland: 175mi</div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="day-body">
            <div style="margin-bottom:10px;">
                <span class="tag tag-forest">🌲 Rainforest</span>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline">
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-time">~Noon</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Depart</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">Seattle via I-5 south → US-12 west → US-101 south. Portland via I-5 north → US-12 west → US-101 south (or US-101 north along coast).</div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-time">~3:00 PM</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Arrive Lake Quinault Area</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">Rendezvous at the Quinault Rain Forest Ranger Station or Lake Quinault Lodge parking area.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-time">3:30–5:30 PM</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Quinault Rain Forest Loop</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc"><strong>Rainforest Nature Trail (0.5mi)</strong> or <strong>Maple Glade Trail (0.5mi)</strong> — easy moss-draped old-growth walks. For more: <strong>Graves Creek Trail</strong> (out-and-back, go as far as time allows).</div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-time">5:30 PM</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Grab firewood & supplies</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">Last gas/supplies in Amanda Park (US-101 & South Shore Rd intersection). Firewood often available at ranger station or roadside.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item camp">
                    <div class="timeline-time">6:00 PM</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Make Camp</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">Head up South Shore Road. Dispersed pulloffs begin ~2 miles past Gatton Creek Campground. River-adjacent, flat sites under conifers.</div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="camp-box">
                <h4>🏕️ Night 1 Camp</h4>
                <div class="primary">Dispersed — South Shore Road / NF-2292 pulloffs</div>
                <div class="backup">Backup: Gatton Creek Campground (first-come, $20/night, vault toilet)</div>
                <div class="coords">📍 ~47.455, -123.735 (general area along South Shore Rd)</div>
            </div>

            <a class="directions-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Seattle,+WA/Lake+Quinault+Lodge,+345+South+Shore+Road,+Quinault,+WA" target="_blank">📍 Google Maps: Seattle → Quinault</a>
            <a class="directions-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Portland,+OR/Lake+Quinault+Lodge,+345+South+Shore+Road,+Quinault,+WA" target="_blank">📍 Google Maps: Portland → Quinault</a>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Day 2 -->
    <div class="day-card">
        <div class="day-header">
            <div class="day-number">2</div>
            <div class="day-title">
                <h3>Coastal Beaches — Kalaloch to Forks</h3>
                <div class="route-text">Quinault → Kalaloch → Ruby Beach → Forks</div>
            </div>
            <div class="day-meta">
                <div class="drive-time">🚗 ~2 hrs total</div>
                <div class="distance">~75 miles</div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="day-body">
            <div style="margin-bottom:10px;">
                <span class="tag tag-ocean">🌊 Ocean</span>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline">
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-time">~Noon</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Break Camp → Head North on US-101</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">Quick 30-min drive from South Shore Road back to US-101 northbound.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-time">12:30 PM</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Kalaloch Beach — Beach 4</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">Short trail to a wild driftwood-strewn beach. Sea stacks, tide pools (check tide tables — low tide is ideal). Easy 0.5mi walk.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-time">2:00 PM</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Ruby Beach</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">The crown jewel. Sea stacks, Abbey Island, crashing surf. 0.2mi trail to beach. Spend 1-2 hours exploring. Best photos at any time with overcast skies.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-time">3:30 PM</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Optional: Beach 3 or Destruction Island Viewpoint</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">Quick pulloffs along 101. Destruction Island viewpoint has whale-watching potential in June (gray whales).</div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-time">4:30 PM</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Continue to Forks — Resupply</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">Forks is the last real town for supplies. Thriftway grocery, gas stations. Stock up for 2 nights.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item camp">
                    <div class="timeline-time">5:30 PM</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Make Camp</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">East of Forks on Sitkum-Sol Duc Road → FS-29. Multiple established dispersed pulloffs in first 5 miles. Flat, forested, truck-friendly.</div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="camp-box">
                <h4>🏕️ Night 2 Camp</h4>
                <div class="primary">Dispersed — FS-29 (Forest Service Road 29), east of Forks</div>
                <div class="backup">Backup: Bogachiel State Park ($25/night, first-come) or Mora Campground (NPS, $20)</div>
                <div class="coords">📍 ~47.92, -124.22 (FS-29 pulloffs, first 5mi)</div>
            </div>

            <a class="directions-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Lake+Quinault,+WA/Ruby+Beach,+WA/Forks,+WA" target="_blank">📍 Google Maps: Quinault → Ruby Beach → Forks</a>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Day 3 -->
    <div class="day-card">
        <div class="day-header">
            <div class="day-number">3</div>
            <div class="day-title">
                <h3>Hoh Rainforest & Rialto Beach</h3>
                <div class="route-text">Forks → Hoh → Rialto Beach → back to Forks</div>
            </div>
            <div class="day-meta">
                <div class="drive-time">🚗 ~1.5 hrs total</div>
                <div class="distance">~55 miles (loop from camp)</div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="day-body">
            <div style="margin-bottom:10px;">
                <span class="tag tag-forest">🌲 Rainforest</span>
                <span class="tag tag-ocean">🌊 Ocean</span>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline">
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-time">~Noon</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Drive to Hoh Rain Forest Visitor Center</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">~45min from FS-29 camp. Take Upper Hoh Road (18mi into the park). Entry fee: $30/vehicle or NPS pass.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-time">1:00 PM</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Hall of Mosses Trail (0.8mi loop)</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">The iconic Olympic experience. Massive bigleaf maples draped in club moss, towering Sitka spruce. Flat, easy, otherworldly. 30-45 minutes.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-time">2:00 PM</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Spruce Nature Trail (1.2mi loop)</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">Loops along the Hoh River. Ancient spruce groves, elk sightings common (especially in meadows near the river). 45 minutes.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-time">3:00 PM</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Drive to Rialto Beach</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">Back to US-101 → La Push Road → Mora Road. ~1hr from Hoh. Dramatic approach through coastal forest.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-time">4:00 PM</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Rialto Beach → Hole-in-the-Wall</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc"><strong>1.5mi one-way beach hike</strong> to the famous sea arch. Stunning at any tide, but passable only at low-mid tide. Check tide chart! Driftwood scrambling. Allow 2 hours round trip.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item camp">
                    <div class="timeline-time">6:30 PM</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Return to FS-29 Camp</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">~30min back from Rialto. Same campsite as Night 2 — no need to break down.</div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="camp-box">
                <h4>🏕️ Night 3 Camp</h4>
                <div class="primary">Dispersed — FS-29 (same site as Night 2)</div>
                <div class="backup">No need to move — settled for two nights.</div>
                <div class="coords">📍 ~47.92, -124.22</div>
            </div>

            <a class="directions-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Forks,+WA/Hoh+Rain+Forest+Visitor+Center,+WA/Rialto+Beach,+WA/Forks,+WA" target="_blank">📍 Google Maps: Day 3 Loop</a>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Day 4 -->
    <div class="day-card">
        <div class="day-header">
            <div class="day-number">4</div>
            <div class="day-title">
                <h3>Hurricane Ridge — Alpine Day</h3>
                <div class="route-text">Forks → Port Angeles → Hurricane Ridge → Camp</div>
            </div>
            <div class="day-meta">
                <div class="drive-time">🚗 ~3 hrs total</div>
                <div class="distance">~115 miles</div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="day-body">
            <div style="margin-bottom:10px;">
                <span class="tag tag-mountain">⛰️ Mountains</span>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline">
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-time">~11:00 AM</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Break Camp — Early Start Recommended</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">Biggest driving day. Leave a bit earlier to maximize ridge time. Forks → Port Angeles via US-101 east (~1.5hrs, scenic along Lake Crescent).</div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-time">12:30 PM</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Lake Crescent — Quick Stop</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">Pull over at the Lake Crescent Lodge viewpoint or Marymere Falls trailhead (0.9mi each way to a 90ft waterfall — optional but stunning).</div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-time">1:30 PM</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Port Angeles — Lunch & Gas</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">Last services before the ridge. Grab lunch downtown (Next Door Gastropub, Kokopelli Grill, or Sabai Thai).</div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-time">2:30 PM</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Drive to Hurricane Ridge (17mi, ~45min)</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">Winding mountain road, gaining 5,200ft. Stop at pullouts for increasingly dramatic views. Entry fee applies (NPS pass).</div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-time">3:15 PM</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Hurricane Ridge Summit (5,242 ft)</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">360° views of Olympic peaks, Strait of Juan de Fuca, and on clear days — Mt. Baker and Vancouver Island. Wildflowers in full bloom mid-June.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-time">3:30 PM</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Hurricane Hill Trail (3.2mi round trip)</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">Paved-then-dirt trail to the summit with 700ft gain. Best panoramic hike on the peninsula. Marmots, deer, wildflower meadows. Allow 1.5-2 hours. <strong>Sunday access = full trail open.</strong></div>
                </div>
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-time">5:30 PM</div>
                    <div class="timeline-title">Descend & Find Camp</div>
                    <div class="timeline-desc">Drive back down toward Port Angeles / Elwha Valley for dispersed options.</div>
